# Example Workflows

The following examples demonstrate common ways to interact with the TQNN API using the official Python SDK.

Replace the example data with your own structured datasets.

---

# EEG

```python
from tqnn import TQNNClient

client = TQNNClient(
    api_key="YOUR_API_KEY"
)

response = client.run_any(
    data=eeg_data,
    mode="EEG",
    task="motor_imagery",
    label="subject_a_session_1",
    metadata={
        "sampling_rate": 250.0
    }
)

print(response["result"])
print(response["tqnn_report"])
```

---

# Tabular Data

```python
from tqnn import TQNNClient

client = TQNNClient(
    api_key="YOUR_API_KEY"
)

dataset = [
    [1.2, 0.4, 3.3, 0.1],
    [2.1, 1.1, 0.9, 0.5],
    [0.7, 0.3, 1.2, 2.1]
]

response = client.run_any(
    data=dataset,
    mode="TABULAR",
    task="fault_diagnosis",
    label="pump_window"
)

print(response["result"])
```

